            <abstract>
                <p>Testimony of Karel Abeles, which became a part of the Documentation campaign,
                    Prague. Abeles is starting his life story in autumn 1938, when he was forced to
                    leave his hometown Teplice in the Czechoslovak borderland. His family moved to
                    Prague, from where they were deported to the Łódź ghetto. Abeles describes the
                    harsh living condition in the ghetto, due to which his parents and brother have
                    died. In 1944 he was deported to Auschwitz-Birkenau, later to Gusen, where he
                    was liberated.</p>
            </abstract>
